        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 10:59PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 1059 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles southeast of Covington, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Brownsville, Covington, Lakeland, Arlington, Whiteville, Somerville,
Brighton, Holly Grove, Hillville, Dancyville, Warren, Oakland, Mason,
Gallaway, Stanton, Braden, Asbury, Yum Yum, Allens, and Belmont.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
